# IPC & preload

## Channel naming

- Format: `domain:action` — e.g. `settings:save`, `db:test-connection`
- Define all channels in `shared/ipc-channels.ts` — no magic strings elsewhere

## Preload

- Expose grouped API via `contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('api', { ... })`
- One file per domain under `preload/api/`
- Return typed promises from `ipcRenderer.invoke`

## Shared

- Types used by main and renderer live in `shared/types/`
- Event constants in `shared/events.ts`

## Security

- Do not expose raw `ipcRenderer` or Node APIs to renderer
- Sanitize errors in main before returning to UI
